      "updated_at": "2016-05-12 13:52:30 UTC",
      "body": "Interesting. It just so happens that `if (` is exactly 4 characters. I personally prefer to align by the opening `(`, but if no-one agrees with me then I am happy to indent at `continuationIndentCallSite` (=4 in default and scala.js styles). I think the IntelliJ formatter and scalariform indent at continuation indent. I'll keep this open a while longer, if no-one comments to agree with me then I'll keep it as you suggest @sjrd."
